libgsm (Jutta Degener / Carsten Bormann, TU Berlin)
---------------------------------------------------

libgsm is the reference GSM 06.10 Full Rate implementation originally
written at Technische Universitaet Berlin. Portions of this crate are
modeled on libgsm primitives and pipeline structure:

  * `src/math.rs` — several fixed-point helpers are modeled on
    libgsm primitives, including `SASR` (signed arithmetic shift
    right), `gsm_norm` (leading-zero count for normalization),
    `gsm_div` (fractional division), and the `L_ACF` autocorrelation
    accumulation (cf. libgsm `src/gsm_*.c`, `src/short_term.c`,
    `src/lpc.c`, `inc/private.h`). The `dp[-120..-1]` history
    addressing convention in the long-term predictor also follows
    libgsm's layout.

  * `src/encoder.rs` — the preprocessing stage (DC offset removal,
    pre-emphasis) and the LPC analysis pipeline (autocorrelation,
    Schur recursion, reflection-coefficient to LAR conversion) are
    structured after libgsm's `src/preprocess.c` and `src/lpc.c`.
    Variable layout, ordering of operations, and intermediate
    scaling choices mirror the reference so that output is
    bit-exact with ETSI 06.10 test vectors.

The ETSI 06.10 normative tables embedded in `src/tables.rs` — INVA,
MIC, MAC, B, QLB, FAC, A, B_TIMES_TWO, DLB, NRFAC, and H — are
spec-defined fixed-point constants drawn from the ETSI/3GPP TS 06.10
standard itself, not from libgsm. They are reproduced here as
required for conformant decode/encode and do not constitute material
derived from libgsm.

